reviews.review_text: THIS IS ONE WEAK SHOW I AM ONE OF THE MANY WHO AGREE WHEN BRENT PASSED AWAY THAT WAS THE BEGINNING OF THE END,AND BY 1994 THE BAND WAS LIVING ON BORROWED TIME AND ABSOLUTELY NO ENERGY OR ANY FEELING IN THE MUSIC.LISTEN TO THE BEGINNING OF SHAKEDOWN WHICH IS OR WAS 1 OF MY FAVORITE SONGS SINCE THE FIRST TIME I SAW IT IN 1978 THE SHAKEDOWN THEY DID AT THIS SHOW WELL IT WASN'T SHAKEDOWN.WELL I COULD GO ON AND ON ABOUT THE LAME 90'S BUT THE MORE I THINK ABOUT THE GRATEFUL DEAD OF THE 90'S THE SADDER I BECOME,SO I JUST GO BACK TO MY FIRST SHOW AT R.P.I UP IN TROY N.Y AND ALL SEEMS FINE WITH THE WORLD.

hoggie has a point all you people who think this was a bad show are crazy first the Grateful Dead had No bad shows.Some may have been better than others.I was at this show and when they opened with your so called weak shakedown the garden went nutts.It may not have been the best sds ever but give me a break its shakedown.Its easy to say now that when brent died it was the beginning of the end, but thats what every body said when pigpen died,so whatever.Vinny came in and was fun.IN my opinion this is a solid show, yes there have been better shows but there have been a lot worse.But then again I don't know everything OR DO I!?!
Way too long at sea... I LUV that someone is calling out for Bobby to open the first set with "Lost Sailor" !  Somethings never changed...
